body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Bryant Auto Group. My name is Austin Bryant. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Madison. Could you provide me with your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's five five five, one two three, four five six seven.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you. And could you also confirm your address with me?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, it's one two three Main Street, Cityville, State.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, I have noted that down. Is there anything else I can assist you with today, Madison?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I was looking for a specific car model on your website, but it seems to be out of stock.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I apologize for the inconvenience, Madison. Thank you for bringing this to our attention. We will look into it further.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time today, Madison. Have a great day!
